    <x:String x:Key="AnimationTitel1">Datatyp Animation</x:String>
    <x:String x:Key="AnimationText1">GM1 animation files consist of a certain number of encoded images and 10 color tables.
        The color tables are used to save space and display different player colors.
        The generated images refer to the currently selected color table:
    </x:String>
    <x:String x:Key="AnimationText2">It is important to note that one color in the picture is taken from the same place in the Colortable, that means in the Picture is for one Pixel one Position for all Colortables.
    The positions of the color in the image remain the same for each Colortable, but the Colortable is changed to give the different player color.
    </x:String>

