    <x:String x:Key="InterfaceTitel1">Datatyp Interface</x:String>
    <x:String x:Key="InterfaceText1">GM1 Interface files consist of a certain number of encoded images.
        These images can be completely edited after export in size and presentation.
        Unfortunately, it is not yet known how a picture is positioned in Stronghold, because the position remains fixed, they can only be extended downwards and to the right.
    </x:String>


    <x:String x:Key="TiledObjectTitel1">Datatyp TiledObject</x:String>
    <x:String x:Key="TiledObjectText1">GM1 files of type TiledObject consist of a certain number of coded pictures.
        These images consist in the GM1 file of many small Diamonds 30 x 16 pixels. The picture below shows such a Diamond enlarged by a factor of 4.
    </x:String>
    <x:String x:Key="TiledObjectText2">From the individual Diamond Tiles then the Grounddiamond of the picture is produced.
    </x:String>

    <x:String x:Key="TiledObjectText3">Finally, pictures with variable height are placed on the individual diamonds and the whole picture is put together.</x:String>


    <x:String x:Key="TiledObjectText4">That means GM1 files of the type TiledObject can only be changed in the height and visually transformed.
        Anything below the Grounddiamond image is ignored, because it need to be isometric.</x:String>

